    "topic": "Department of Posts Launches DHRUVA: India’s National Digital Address Infrastructure",
    "subtopics": [
      {
        "subtopic": "Department of Posts Launches DHRUVA: India’s National Digital Address Infrastructure",
        "content": "• The Department of Posts (DoP) has introduced a comprehensive policy framework for DHRUVA, a Digital Address Digital Public Infrastructure (DPI) designed to provide a unique and precise digital address for every home in India.\n• About DHRUVA:\n  o A DPI that creates a secure, geo-coded digital address system for homes across India.\n  o Enables users to share accurate address information through a standardized geo-spatial framework.\n  o Recognizes address management as essential for effective governance and enhanced user experiences.\n• Two Key Layers:\n  1. Digital Postal Index Number (DIGIPIN):\n    o A 10-digit alpha-numeric code based on geographic coordinates (latitude-longitude).\n    o Developed by dividing India’s territory into uniform grids of approximately 4×4 meters.\n    o Provides unique location identification using geospatial data.\n  2. Digital Address Layer:\n    o A user-centric, consent-based system built on DIGIPIN.\n    o Allows users to create personalized labels linked to their DIGIPIN and descriptive address."
